HAZYVIEW –  According to police spokesman Capt Dineo Sekgotodi, the operation began yesterday, and led to the six arrests.  There are unconfirmed reports that this is part of the largest police operation against rhino poaching countrywide. “While the investigation was ongoing, one of the suspects owes SARS R21 million.” The Hawks are currently busy confiscating assests belonging to the accused.  All six are expected to appear in the White River Magistrate’s Court later today.